LSF
```json
{
  "application": "LSF",
  "description": "The script uses the LSF (Load Sharing Facility) batch system to submit and manage jobs. It defines various parameters for the job, including:

* **-J p1_NKTMAIT_v6**: Job name
* **-q highmem**: Queue to submit the job to (high memory queue)
* **-W 24:00**: Walltime (maximum runtime) for the job (24 hours)
* **-n 1**: Number of nodes to run on (1)
* **-M 500**: Memory limit for each node (500 MB)
* **-R rusage[mem=500]**: Resource request (memory 500 MB)
* **-B**: Don't send job notifications (optional)
* **-N**: Don't send job notifications (optional)
* **-u ychu2@mdanderson.org**: User email for job notifications
* **-o**: Standard output file path
* **-e**: Standard error file path
* **-cwd**: Working directory

The script also loads specific modules (python/3.7.3-anaconda and R/3.6.0) using the 'module load' command. The 'run.sh' script appears to be a utility for running UMAP and clustering analysis based on the provided parameters and input data."
}
```
